g.text: Bootstrap ClassLoader :- Load rt,jar which contains all the class files of java standard edition
like java.lang, package, java.net, java.util, java.io
Extension ClassLoader :- It loads the jar from which is located inside
System/Application ClassLoader :- It load the classfiles from classpath default is current directory.
Path can be changed by (-cp) and (-classpath).
Stores per class structures such as runtime constant pool, field, method, code of method.
It's a runtime data area in which objects are allocated.
It stores frame. it hold local variable and partial result and play part in method invocation and return.
Hold address of instruction currently being executed.
It contains all the native method used in application
2) Interprator read the bytecode stream then execute instructions
3) JIT(Just in Time compiler) compile parts of the bytecode having similar functionality at same time.
It translate JVM instruction to instruction set of specific cpu.
JNI (Java Native Interface) is a framework which provides an interface
to communicate with another application written in c, c++ etc. It sends
output to console or interact with OS libraries.
